<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The specific epithet is derived from the Latin for coppery, referring to the colour of the abdomen, which has a weak metallic lustre.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
