<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The head (particularly the gena) and genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lonsdale" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia cuprea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuprea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of the Californian 
<taxonomicName family="Agromyzidae" genus="O." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="O. delecta" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="delecta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">O. delecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spencer (
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Handbook" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 478" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" refId="B261" refString="Spencer, KA, Steyskal, GC, 1986b. Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U.S.D.A. Agriculture Handbook 638: 1 - 478, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" title="Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U. S. D. A." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" volume="638" year="1986 b">Spencer and Steyskal 1986b</bibRefCitation>
: figs 271, 272), but 
<taxonomicName family="Agromyzidae" genus="O." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="O. delecta" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="delecta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">O. delecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having eight rows of acrostichal setulae (not five to six), a black (not coppery) abdomen and a facial bulb that is much narrower than the pedicel (
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="University of California, Division of Agricultural Sciences, Special Publication" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 489" refId="B253" refString="Spencer, KA, 1981. A revisionary study of the leaf-mining flies (Agromyzidae) of California. University of California, Division of Agricultural Sciences, Special Publication 3273: 1 - 489" title="A revisionary study of the leaf-mining flies (Agromyzidae) of California." volume="3273" year="1981">Spencer 1981</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, based on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Spencer’s">Spencer's</normalizedToken>
illustration, the distiphallus of that species is more broadly rounded basally and atrophied apically. 
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="University of California, Division of Agricultural Sciences, Special Publication" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 489" refId="B253" refString="Spencer, KA, 1981. A revisionary study of the leaf-mining flies (Agromyzidae) of California. University of California, Division of Agricultural Sciences, Special Publication 3273: 1 - 489" title="A revisionary study of the leaf-mining flies (Agromyzidae) of California." volume="3273" year="1981">Spencer (1981)</bibRefCitation>
also describes the similar 
<taxonomicName family="Agromyzidae" genus="O." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="O. definita" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="definita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">O. definita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spencer (later provided the new name 
<taxonomicName family="Agromyzidae" genus="O." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="O. subdefinita" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="subdefinita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">O. subdefinita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spencer; 
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Handbook" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 478" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" refId="B261" refString="Spencer, KA, Steyskal, GC, 1986b. Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U.S.D.A. Agriculture Handbook 638: 1 - 478, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" title="Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U. S. D. A." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" volume="638" year="1986 b">Spencer and Steyskal 1986b</bibRefCitation>
: figs 268, 269) in his Californian revision, but the fasciculus is straight (not curved), the abdomen is also black and the distiphallus is much paler; the number of rows of acrostichal setulae are not mentioned, but it is indicated that there are also eight.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
